Definition.WordDefinition:
Holographic \Hol`o*graph"ic\, a. 1. Of the nature of a holograph; pertaining to holographs. [1913 Webster]
2. Of or pertaining to holography or holograms; produced by holography. [PJC]

holographic adj 1: of or relating to holography or holograms 2: written entirely in one's own hand; "holographic document" [syn: {holographical}] 3: written wholly in the handwriting of the signer; "a holographic will"
